  <brief_title>Preoperative Immunonutrition in Normonourished Patients Undergoing Fast-track Laparoscopic Colorectal Surgery</brief_title>
  <official_title>Preoperative Immunonutrition Versus Standard Dietary Advice in Normo-nourished Patients Undergoing Fast-track Laparoscopic Colorectal Surgery</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>University of Rome Tor Vergata</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University of Rome Tor Vergata</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <is_fda_regulated_drug>No</is_fda_regulated_drug>
    <is_fda_regulated_device>No</is_fda_regulated_device>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Immunonutrition (IN) appears to reduce infective complications and in-hospital length of stay&#xD;
      (LOS) after gastrointestinal surgery. More specifically, it seems to be beneficial also in&#xD;
      colorectal cancer surgery. Potential benefits of combining preoperative IN (PIN) with&#xD;
      protocols of enhanced recovery after surgery (ERAS) in reducing LOS in laparoscopic surgery&#xD;
      are yet to be determined.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
